news.title: Ahmedabad civic body seals 257 properties of tax defaulters
news.para: ​​Additionally, notices were issued to some defaulters urging them to pay their outstanding taxes promptly.

news.title: Telangana HC directs state govt to release 40 crore in property tax charges to SCB
news.para: The ruling marks a significant win for the cantonment board, bringing the total amount received to nearly 90 crore out of the estimated 100 crore due. Previously, the board had received 48 crore in March.

news.title: West Bengal government grants 4 crore for 4,500 LED streetlights in Salt Lake and Rajarhat-Gopalpur
news.para: BMC will install 405 LED lights with 90-watt capacity using Rs 1.7 crore and 4,060 LED lights of 45 and 60-watt capacity with Rs 2.1 crore.

news.title: Nashik civic body gets 22,000 new properties under tax net in nine months
news.para: Owners of these properties must pay the tax either from the past two years or the year that construction started for their properties. Hence, the civic body will get an additional Rs 20 crore revenue through these new properties.

news.title: GCCI criticizes hike in minimum land prices for Mormugao
news.para: The GCCI said that govt has increased minimum land rates from 597% to 2,857%, which is exorbitant, unreasonable and unfair.

news.title: Surat civic body revenue from paid FSI hits Rs 829 crore in nine months
news.para: By the end of the financial year, the total amount is likely to cross Rs 1,100 crore, according to SMC officials. The yearly earnings are almost double of the revenue three years ago.

news.title: GIS mapping to make ready reckoner rates more accurate in Maharashtra
news.para: We estimate that 50% of the work in urban and urban-influence areas is done. We should be able to use this data in deciding the RR rates, as it gives a clear idea of the area," said a senior official from the registration department.

news.title: Buyers demand FTL and buffer zone maps before finalising properties in Hyderabad
news.para: They share how prospective buyers are increasingly prioritising due diligence over aesthetics, asking for approval documents and FTL maps before committing.

news.title: Gurugram civic body penalises builder for flouting construction curbs
news.para: When the team monitored Zone-2, they found construction work ongoing at the site in Sector 113 despite the ban.

news.title: SC directs ED to attach assets of JP Morgan for violation of FEMA in Amrapali Group case
news.para: ED said it has prima facie found that there was violation of FEMA norms by the US-based JP Morgan and a complaint in this regard has been lodged.

news.title: UltraTech Cement gets CCI's approval to acquire majority stake in India Cements
news.para: The fair trade regulator also granted its clearance to UltraTech Cement to acquire up to 26 per cent of the paid-up equity share capital of India Cements by way of an open offer, it added.

news.title: Shree Cement to invest Rs 1,100 crore to set up cement plant in Purnea
news.para: The Bangur family-promoted company is among the top five cement producers in the country.

news.title: CAG audit finds lapses in YEIDA's policies
news.para: All these lapses have added up and manifested today as the country's biggest stalled projects problem – if YEIDA, Noida and Greater Noida are taken together – that different kinds of govt and court interventions have found hard to crack.

news.title: Ventive Hospitality IPO subscribed 71% on Day 1
news.para: The category for Qualified Institutional Buyers (QIBs) got 1.05 times subscription while the portion for Retail Individual Investors (RIIs) received 61 per cent subscription. Non-Institutional Investors part got subscribed 10 per cent.

news.title: Hyderabad: ED raids realty firms over money laundering allegations
news.para: The total seizure value was approximately 6.1 crore. Incriminating documents related to suspicious and unaccounted cash transactions, as well as property documents, were also seized.

news.title: Telangana RERA imposes Rs 11 lakh penalty on Paradise Peak for non-registration
news.para: The penalty follows a complaint filed by a buyer, M Santhosh, who alleged irregularities in the sale of plots without the mandatory registration.

news.title: Sattva Group acquires 8.5 acre land parcel for Rs 300 crore in Bengaluru
news.para: The property, which previously housed the operations of global healthcare major Novo Nordisk India, has been a landmark in the area for over a decade. Novo Nordisk had operated from the campus for over 10 years before transitioning out.

news.title: Goa: Occupancy certificate withheld for Calapur project over environmental concerns
news.para: The HC told the deputy solicitor general of India to take instructions on the aspect of the relaxation of the setback for the project, as the petitioner’s counsel, Rohit Bras de Sa, told the HC that only central govt is empowered to grant such a relaxation.

news.title: Innov8 launches two lakh sq ft flexible spaces in Mumbai and Navi Mumbai
news.para: Q Parc - is located along the Thane-Belapur Road in Ghansoli with a total seating capacity of 1,500 while Innov8 Zion – the Andheri center has a total seating capacity of 1,500.

news.title: Madhu Mantena acquires three apartments for Rs 25.75 crore in Mumbai’s Juhu
news.para: Madhu Mantena’s productions include Ghajini (2008), Queen (2015), Masaan and many more.
